China will boost investments in
building fiber optic and faster wireless networks to help
stimulate consumption and drive economic growth, according to a
statement on the central governmentâ€™s website today.
* Under the so-called Broadband China Strategic Plan, the
country will ensure half of its households have broadband access
by 2015 and 32.5% of cellular users will have access to 3G or
other fast networks: statement
* Current broadband speed will also be increased: statement
* Plan to be implemented by investments through relevant
